The paper presents a new theory for general artificial intelligence, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.AI category. The paper also discusses the development of a new Agent that is capable of solving Atari games more efficiently than other techniques, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also mentions the application of the theory to other areas such as non-linear control theory, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. The paper also discusses the use of cellular automaton-like structures to model information, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper mentions the application of the theory to information theory, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.IT (Information Theory) category.
